		<h2 class="rules">Rules of the Totalizator</h2>
		<section>
			<h4>General provisions</h4>
			<p>
				<b> Totalizator</b> - it is a game and an institution where the organizer on
    			the basis of rules of a totalizator and regulating this type of activity
    			legislations accepts cash rates from participants for the outcomes
    			the competitions provided by a totalizator, distributes according to
    			governed the money (pool) received in the form of rates between
    			the won participants, deducting itself the fixed interest (the income
    			totalizator) for compensation of expenses and profit earning.
			</p>
			<p>
				<b>Participant of a totalizator</b> - the physical person which relied in
    			totalizator in an order and on the conditions determined by the presents
    			rules. The participant of a totalizator shall be not younger than 18 years.
			</p>
			<p>
				<b>Event</b> – here the same that match, competition. A rate in
   				 totalizator - set of outcomes of events (on one of everyone
   				 match of the next totalizator) on which the participant puts money, and
   				 also size of this sum of money. The participant wins at the rate,
   				 if in it results of 12 and more events are guessed, and loses,
    			 if less than 12 events are guessed. In case of loss the rate is lost, in case of
   				 prize - enters payment to the participant from prize fund as it
   				 component.
			</p>
			<b>Pool</b> - the sum of money received in the form of rates of participants on
  					 another draw of a totalizator.
		</section>

		<section>
			<h4>Rules of calculation of prize fund</h4>
			<p>
				<b>Prize fund</b> - the part of a pool (90%) intended for payment
    				prizes. The prize fund is divided into 4 advantageous categories:
			</p>
			<ul>
				<li>The first category –<b>20% of a pool</b>, in distribution of this
    		 parts of prize fund participate rates in which are guessed
     		 results of 15 events.
				</li>
				<li>The second category – <b>15% of a pool</b>, in distribution
     			all rates where results of 15 or 14 events are guessed participate.
				</li>
				<li>The third category – <b>20% of a pool</b>, in distribution
     			all rates where results of 15, 14 or 13 events are guessed participate.
				</li>
				<li>The fourth category – <b>35% of a pool</b>, in distribution
    		    all rates where results 15, 14, 13 or 12 are guessed participate
     			events.
				</li>
				<li>Jackpot - an additional prize which is distributed
     			among rates where results of 15 matches are guessed.</li>
			</ul>
		</section>
